%N A121848 The spiral parameter gamma for the icosahedral fullerenes.
%C A121848 Icosahedral fullerenes are ordered by increasing number of carbon atoms, then increasing Goldberg parameter i, and finally increasing Goldberg parameter j. For parameters 0 <= j <= i, then corresponding number of carbon atoms is m = 20 * (i^2 + i*j + j^2). - _Sean A. Irvine_, Jul 13 2026
%H A121848 P. W. Fowler and K. M. Rogers, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1021/ci9901486">Spiral Codes and Goldberg Representations of Icosahedral Fullerenes and Octahedral Analogues</a>, J. Chem. Inf. Comput. Sci., vol. 41 (2001) 108-111.
%F A121848 a(n) = (5*i+1) * (i-1) + j * (5*i-3) where i and j are the Goldberg parameters [see Fowler and Rogers]. - _Sean A. Irvine_, Jul 13 2026
%e A121848 If m=80 then gamma is 11.
%e A121848 If m=500 then gamma is 104.
%Y A121848 Cf. A121847, A121849.
